<exercise checkit-seed="0045" checkit-slug="G1" checkit-title="Row operations and determinants">
  <statement>
    <p>Let <m>A</m> be a <m>4 \times 4</m> matrix with determinant <m> -3 </m>.</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Let <m>M</m> be the matrix obtained from <m>A</m> by applying the row operation <m> R_2 \leftrightarrow R_1 </m>.
              What is <m>\operatorname{det}\ M</m>?</li>
      <li>Let <m>Q</m> be the matrix obtained from <m>A</m> by applying the row operation <m> R_1 \to -2R_1 </m>.
              What is <m>\operatorname{det}\ Q</m>?</li>
      <li>Let <m>C</m> be the matrix obtained from <m>A</m> by applying the row operation <m> R_3 \to R_3 + -2R_4 </m>.
              What is <m>\operatorname{det}\ C</m>?</li>
    </ol>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <m>\operatorname{det}\ M= 3 </m>
      </li>
      <li>
        <m>\operatorname{det}\ Q= 6 </m>
      </li>
      <li>
        <m>\operatorname{det}\ C= -3 </m>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </answer>
</exercise>

